    "body": "The methods should be added in the [`modules/hardhat.ts`](https://github.com/NomicFoundation/hardhat/blob/main/packages/hardhat-core/src/internal/hardhat-network/provider/modules/hardhat.ts) file, which in turn will need some changes in the [HardhatNode](https://github.com/NomicFoundation/hardhat/blob/main/packages/hardhat-core/src/internal/hardhat-network/provider/node.ts) class.\r\n\r\nThat's very straightforward to do. The tricky part is to add tests for this. The tests should be in [this file](https://github.com/NomicFoundation/hardhat/blob/main/packages/hardhat-core/test/internal/hardhat-network/provider/modules/hardhat.ts) and should cover a couple of scenarios:\r\n\r\n1. Disable the option, send 3 or 4 txs, check that they are all the blocks have a different timestamp\r\n2. Disable the option, use `evm_setNextBlockTimestamp` with the timestamp of the latest block, you should get an error\r\n3. Enable the option, send 3 or 4 txs, check that their timestamps are the same or have a difference of at most 1. (See [this test](https://github.com/NomicFoundation/hardhat/blob/main/packages/hardhat-core/test/internal/hardhat-network/provider/node.ts) for example.)\r\n4. Enable the option, use `evm_setNextBlockTimestamp` with the timestamp of the latest block, you should get an error`, you shouldn't get an error. Then calling `hardhat_mine` should mine a new block whose timestamp is the same as the one in the previous block.",
